HEADWORD: Gesso duro
<hw>Ges"so du"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It., hard plaster.]</ety>
<def>A variety of gesso which when dried becomes hard and durable, often
used in making bas-relief casts, which are colored and mounted in
elaborate frames.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

